==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Papula
<hw>Pap"u*la</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Papul⟦ae⟧</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[L.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>A pimple; a small, usually
conical, elevation of the cuticle, produced by congestion, accumulated
secretion, or hypertrophy of tissue; a papule.</def>
<rj><au>Quain.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>One of the numerous small hollow
processes of the integument between the plates of starfishes.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Papular</ent>⟦br⟧
